item.title: What music do you listen to most?
item.dc:creator: @the_bank the bank
item.description:
@the_bank wrote:

I pride myself on a rather large music appreciation.

I can usually stand just about anything except for country and rap. Having said that, I also have problems with *core (yes I know it’s generic but anything *core I am yet to like so far). What some people refer to as screamo I also dislike. Last but not least I can’t stand Numetal as it is too close to rap.

Other than that I like a little bit of everything. Doom metal and black metal aren’t usually my first choices however they are there. Classic rock and punk rock are big for me. If I’m in the mood I have no problem with listening to some blues or classical music. Deathmetal is by far my number one genre however I have an appreciation and a liking for most metal genres. I even find myself listening to hardstyle and house music sometimes.

EDIT: I’d also like to specifically acknowledge Thrash for all of its excellent pieces.
